		<p>To be precise: the Christian convert who collected the stories was a Kunama man from Kulluku near Gash river (Soona) named Joseph Fufa Mati (the Rev. August Andersson was the supervisor). According to my findings in Sweden the collection was formed round the beginning of the first world war. Your translation is acceptable (relatives= matrilineal kin= kebese in Kunama language)</p>

		<div class="reply">
				</div>
